<paragraph id="513473592C108E674B54F9B9FB88F9EF" blockId="10.[249,1081,1611,1658]" box="[275,1081,1611,1632]" pageId="10" pageNumber="309">
This subspecies has been recorded from 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C108E6748FAF9B9FCBAF9EF" box="[701,779,1611,1632]" country="United States of America" name="Indiana" pageId="10" pageNumber="309">Indiana</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C108E674969F9B9FC19F9EF" box="[814,936,1611,1632]" country="United States of America" name="Mississippi" pageId="10" pageNumber="309">Mississippi</collectingRegion>
, west through
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="199120D22C108E664ABEF997FCC5FD4E" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="310" pageId="10" pageNumber="309" type="description">
<paragraph id="513473592C108E664ABEF997FB98FE19" blockId="10.[249,1081,1611,1658]" lastBlockId="11.[241,1073,277,705]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="310" pageId="10" pageNumber="309">
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C108E674ABEF997FE88F9F5" box="[249,313,1637,1658]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="10" pageNumber="309">Texas</collectingRegion>
. Records from 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C108E674BB6F997FDF4F9F5" box="[497,581,1637,1658]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="10" pageNumber="309">Arizona</collectingRegion>
and Lower 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C108E67489CF997FCF4F9F5" box="[731,837,1637,1658]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="10" pageNumber="309">California</collectingRegion>
listed in 
<bibRefCitation id="351A0EA82C108E6649F9F997FE86FEA5" author="Chamberlin" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="310" pageId="10" pageNumber="309" refId="ref7854" refString="Chamberlin, W. J. 1926. Catalogue of the Buprestidae of North America north of Mexico. Corvallis, Oregon. 289 p." type="book" year="1926">Chamberlin (1926)</bibRefCitation>
were referred to 
<taxonomicName id="968B08DA2C118E664BB2FEE4FC8DFEA5" authority="Schaeffer" authorityName="Schaeffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[501,828,277,299]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpureoplagiata">
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E664BB2FEE4FD7FFEA4" box="[501,718,278,299]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">C. purpureoplagiata</emphasis>
Schaeffer
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="351A0EA82C118E66492EFEE7FC4DFEA5" author="Fisher" box="[873,1020,277,298]" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" pagination="1 - 275" refId="ref7913" refString="Fisher, W. S. 1942. A revision of the North American species of buprestid beetles belonging to the tribe Chrysobothrini. U. S. Department of Agriculture Miscellaneous Publication 470: 1 - 275." type="journal article" year="1942">Fisher (1942)</bibRefCitation>
. The following specimens represent a 
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E66480AFEC2FCB9FECA" bold="true" box="[589,776,304,325]" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">new state record</emphasis>
from 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C118E66490EFEC2FC67FECA" box="[841,982,304,325]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
: Lincoln Co., Valley of Fires, 
<quantity id="9673DEBC2C118E664B9CFEB9FD80FEEF" box="[475,561,331,352]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.585" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" unit="m" value="1585.0">1585 m</quantity>
, 11­VII­84, on 
<taxonomicName id="968B08DA2C118E664899FEBEFCF7FEEF" box="[734,838,331,353]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cannabaceae" genus="Celtis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E664899FEBEFCAAFEEE" box="[734,795,332,353]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">Celtis</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
; Otero Co., 
<quantity id="9673DEBC2C118E664996FEB9FBB4FEEF" box="[977,1029,331,352]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.218688" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" unit="mi" value="2.0">2 mi</quantity>
NE Mayhill, 12­VII­84, on 
<taxonomicName id="968B08DA2C118E664BB7FE94FCAFFEF4" authority="Raf." authorityName="Raf." box="[496,798,358,379]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cercocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E664BB7FE94FD57FEF4" box="[496,742,358,379]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">Cercocarpus montanus</emphasis>
Raf.
</taxonomicName>
, both RLWE. It has been reared from several hosts, and the adults are collected on many other plants.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="513473592C118E664B4CFE6EFCC5FD4E" blockId="11.[241,1073,277,705]" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">
<bibRefCitation id="351A0EA82C118E664B4CFE6EFE2EFE3E" author="Cazier" box="[267,415,412,433]" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref7827" refString="Cazier, M. A. 1951. The Buprestidae of north central Mexico (Coleoptera). American Museum Novitates 1526: 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1951">Cazier (1951)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="968B08DA2C118E66484AFE6EFD57FE3E" authorityName="Schaeffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[525,742,412,433]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpureoplagiata">
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E66484AFE6EFD57FE3E" box="[525,742,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">C. purpureoplagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C118E66496BFE6EFC11FE3E" box="[812,928,412,433]" country="Mexico" name="Chihuahua" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">Chihuahua</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C118E6649EAFE6EFBB1FE3E" box="[941,1024,412,433]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">Mexico</collectingRegion>
. His description of the 
<specimenCount id="478DB8D02C118E664BF0FE45FDE4FE43" box="[439,597,439,460]" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
available for study leaves no doubt that instead it should be 
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E664BF8FE20FD1AFE68" box="[447,683,466,487]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicName id="968B08DA2C118E664BF8FE20FD19FE68" box="[447,680,466,487]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="purpureovittata" subSpecies="purpureovittata">C. p. purpureovittata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This and a specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="968B08DA2C118E664984FE20FEC0FD8C" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="purpureovittata" subSpecies="purpureovittata">
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E664984FE20FEC0FD8C" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">C. p. purpureovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C118E664BF2FE1FFD8AFD8D" box="[437,571,493,514]" country="Mexico" name="Nuevo Leon" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">Nuevo Leon</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity id="9673DEBC2C118E66480FFE1FFDC8FD8D" box="[584,633,493,514]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.828032" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" unit="mi" value="3.0">3 mi</quantity>
S Montemorelos, 23­VI­71, RLWE, represent a 
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E664B0CFDFAFDE2FD92" bold="true" box="[331,595,520,541]" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">
new record for 
<collectingCountry id="299C33C92C118E664BBCFDFAFDFFFD92" box="[507,590,520,541]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
This is consistent with our knowledge of the distribution of these species and the occurrence of like forms of the latter in Big Bend National Park, Texas, which borders 
<collectingRegion id="934FBDBB2C118E664944FDCDFCC9FDDB" box="[771,888,575,596]" country="Mexico" name="Chihuahua" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">Chihuahua</collectingRegion>
. Given the wide distribution of 
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E664BD3FDA8FDD0FDE0" box="[404,609,602,623]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">
<taxonomicName id="968B08DA2C118E664BD3FDA8FDEFFDE0" authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1886" box="[404,606,602,623]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpureovittata">C. purpureovittata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
it is not surprising that it exhibits a great deal of variation. In fact, the limits between this species and 
<taxonomicName id="968B08DA2C118E6649C2FD84FE96FD29" authorityName="Schaeffer" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="310" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpureoplagiata">
<emphasis id="63FFAF4B2C118E6649C2FD84FE96FD29" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="310">C. purpureoplagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not well defined, with populations going under that name being highly variable too. This area is fertile ground for further study.
</paragraph>
